176.  (1) In proceedings under this Chapter the Court shall keep a
record of the particulars of each case by using and completing or
causing to be completed a charge sheet in accordance with such forms
as the Chief Judge may direct and, where all necessary particulars
cannot conveniently be entered on any such form, by annexing to it any
requisite number of continuation sheets.
(2) The particulars to be incorporated in the record shall include:
(a) the name of the Court and the serial number of the case;
(b) the name and, where female, the sex of the accused;
(c) the address of the accused;
(d) the charge;
(e) the return date of the summons, if any;
